0India%20than%20earning%20through%20its%20export%2C%20even%20as%20the%20country%20aims%20to%20become%20a%20net%20exporter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20domestic%20production%20declines%20sharply%20in%20the%20dry%20season%20requiring%20power%20supply%20from%20the%20southern%20neighbour%2C%20the%20Nepal%20Electricity%20Authority%20(NEA)%20has%20been%20forced%20to%20spend%20big%20on%20buying%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20NEA%2C%20it%20spent%20as%20much%20Rs%201%2C944%20crore%20to%20buy%20power%20from%20India%20while%20its%20export%20to%20the%20southern%20neighbour%20stood%20at%20Rs%201%2C010%20crore%20in%20the%20last%20fiscal%20year%202022-23%2C%20suggesting%20the%20country%20still%20has%20a%20long%20way%20to%20go%20to%20be%20self-reliant%20in%20clean%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENepal%20exported%20power%20equivalent%20to%201%2C333%20gigawatt%20hours%20in%20the%20last%20fiscal%20while%20it%20imported%201%2C833%20gigawatt%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProlonged%20drought%20in%20the%20last%20fiscal%20year%20badly%20affected%20domestic%20power%20generation%20and%20the%20country%20had%20to%20import%20more%2C%20said%20Kul%20Man%20Ghising%2C%20managing%20director%20of%20the%20NEA.%20%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20result%2C%20Nepal%20continues%20to%20become%20a%20net%20importer.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStating%20that%20the%20country%20faced%20an%20unprecedented%20fall%20in%20power%20generation%2C%20the%20NEA%20decided%20to%20procure%20power%20through%20bids%20from%20Indian%20generators%20and%20traders%20with%20the%20hope%20that%20competition%20would%20significantly%20lower%20the%20purchase%20price%20of%20electricity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20since%20the%20lowest%20bid%20prices%20exceeded%20the%20average%20price%20trends%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20day-ahead%20power%20exchange%20market%2C%20the%20NEA%20was%20bound%20to%20annul%20the%20bidding%20process%20and%20cling%20to%20a%20bilateral%20agreement%20with%20the%20Indian%20power%20traders%20for%20the%20months%20of%20March%2C%20April%20and%20May%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20power%20utility%20said%20in%20its%20Annual%20Report%202022-23.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20fiscal%20year%202019-20%2C%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20power%20import%20has%20been%20on%20a%20downward%20trend%20amid%20increasing%20domestic%20power%20generation%20in%20the%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGhising%20said%20that%20he%20believes%20power%20imports%20will%20continue%20to%20decline%20even%20though%20the%20country%20had%20to%20import%20more%20due%20to%20prolonged%20drought.%20%E2%80%9CStill%2C%20net%20import%20decreased%20even%20in%20the%20last%20fiscal%20year%2C%20even%20though%20total%20imports%20increased%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NEA%20aims%20to%20be%20self-reliant%20on%20electricity%20by%202026.%20Ghising%20said%20it%20was%20possible%20to%20meet%20this%20target%20considering%20the%20planned%20generation%20of%20the%20electricity%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%20the%20current%20fiscal%20year%202022-23%2C%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20power%20generation%20capacity%20is%20expected%20to%20reach%202%2C853%20MW%2C%204%2C507%20MW%20by%20mid-July%202024%20and%205%2C251%20MW%20in%20mid-July%202025%2C%20according%20to%20the%20power%20utility.%20But%20domestic%20consumption%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20half%20the%20potential%20generation%20by%202025%2C%20forcing%20Nepal%20to%20sell%20electricity%20abroad%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20all%20the%20planned%20projects%20are%20completed%20by%202026%2C%20Nepal%20has%20every%20chance%20of%20becoming%20self-reliant%20on%20electricity%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Sher%20Singh%20Bhat%2C%20former%20deputy%20managing%20director%20of%20the%20NEA.%20%E2%80%9CProvided%20Nepal%20achieves%20generation%20capacity%20of%20around%205%2C500%20MW%2C%20there%20can%20be%20base%20load%20demand%20for%20around%202%2C000%20MW%20in%20the%20dry%20season%20which%20Nepal%20can%20meet%20with%20its%20own%20generation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcc