o%20global%20business%2C%20it%20will%20no%20longer%20be%20the%20lodestar%20for%20growth.%20It%20will%20still%20advance%2C%20but%20much%20more%20slowly.%20And%20while%20those%20on%20the%20outside%20will%20still%20be%20able%20to%20observe%20the%20economy%2C%20it%20will%20become%20increasingly%20difficult%20to%20truly%20understand%20what's%20going%20on%20within.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%20of%20China's%20blob%20era%20pushed%20its%20way%20to%20the%20center%20of%20the%20global%20news%20cycle%20earlier%20this%20month%20when%20the%20Chinese%20government%20announced%20that%20it%20would%20no%20longer%20publish%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20for%20young%20people%20as%20part%20of%20its%20monthly%20jobs%20report.%20The%20final%20release%20for%20the%20data%20series%20%E2%80%94%20July's%20number%20%E2%80%94%20came%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinese-young-adults-gdp-graduates-university-economy-rate-unemployment-2023-8%3Fop%3D1%5C%22%3Eat%20a%20record%20high%20of%2020.5%25.%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20number%20had%20become%20a%20global%20shorthand%20for%20China's%20inability%20to%20reignite%20its%20economy%20since%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20ended%20the%20country's%20draconian%20COVID-19%20lockdowns.%20So%20now%20it's%20gone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sudden%20disappearance%20of%20the%20youth-unemployment%20report%20generated%20headlines%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20a%20shock%20for%20longtime%20China%20watchers.%20Data%20has%20been%20disappearing%20from%20all%20over%20the%20country%20for%20years%20now.%20Reports%20detailing%20everything%20from%20exports%20to%20cement%20production%20%E2%80%94%20which%20are%20arguably%20more%20crucial%20for%20understanding%20the%20country's%20structural%20malaise%20than%20youth%20unemployment%20%E2%80%94%20have%20vanished%20or%20become%20corrupted%20to%20the%20point%20that%20they're%20no%20longer%20useful.%20This%20is%20not%20happening%20just%20because%20the%20economy%20is%20slowing%3B%20plenty%20of%20countries%20continue%20publishing%20data%20even%20though%20it's%20no%20longer%20rosy.%20This%20is%20happening%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-covid-lockdown-protests-economy-recession-crisis-2022-11%5C%22%3EXi's%20China%20is%20one%20that%20puts%20ideology%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20economic%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party's%20primary%20focus%20was%20to%20develop%20the%20economy%2C%20and%20more%20recently%2C%20to%20turn%20the%20Chinese%20consumer%20into%20a%20dynamic%20force%20of%20global%20demand.%20That%20transition%20required%20major%20reforms%20in%20how%20China%20operated%20its%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20slowly%20opening%20it%20up%20and%20giving%20it%20a%20more%20bottom-up%20structure%20in%20which%20individuals%20make%20more%20choices%20about%20their%20livelihoods.%20But%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jiinping-future-tech-global-economy-semiconductors-military-failing-2022-9%5C%22%3Eyears%20of%20fueling%20China's%20rise%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20these%20efforts%20have%20been%20stopped%20in%20their%20tracks.%20Not%20because%20the%20reforms%20weren't%20working%2C%20but%20because%20the%20China%20they%20were%20creating%20is%20not%20the%20one%20Xi%20wants%20to%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20even%20know%20that%20it%20is%20possible%20to%20move%20to%20a%20private%2C%20domestic%2C%20demand-driven%20economy%20in%20China%2C%20given%20how%20it%20directly%20conflicts%20with%20the%20top-down%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20party%20typically%20manages%20the%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Charlene%20Chu%2C%20the%20managing%20Director%20and%20senior%20analyst%20at%20Autonomous%20Research%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt%20would%20take%20a%20sea%20change%20in%20thinking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-debt-economy-implode-stock-market-wall-street-xi-jinping-2023-6%5C%22%3Emain%20drivers%20of%20China's%20economy%20stumble%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20will%20be%20no%20direct%20support%20to%20help%20households%20power%20through%20this%20fragile%20period.%20Xi%20has%20been%20telling%20his%20people%20to%20prepare%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Bstruggle%2C%26quot%3B%20to%20be%20ready%20to%20put%20geopolitical%20concerns%20over%20economic%20ones%20for%20the%20foreseeable%20future.%20This%20is%20bad%20news%20for%20multinational%20corporations%C2%A0%20%E2%80%94%20companies%20like%20Nike%20and%20Starbucks%C2%A0%20%E2%80%94%20that%20banked%20on%20a%20growing%2C%20opening%20China.%20And%20it's%20bad%20news%20for%20investors%20who've%20been%20waiting%20for%20China's%20growth%20to%20return%20to%20something%20like%20it%20was%20before%20the%20pandemic.%20The%20economy%20has%20been%20showing%20signs%20of%20a%20structural%20slowdown%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20but%20the%20strain%20on%20the%20system%20has%20become%20so%20great%20that%20the%20market%20can%20no%20longer%20ignore%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20struggles%20that%20China%20faces%20are%20real%20%E2%80%94%20economic%20pain%2C%20foreign-investor%20concerns%2C%20crumbling%20demographics%20%E2%80%94%20but%20in%20the%20face%20of%20these%20challenges%2C%20it's%20clear%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpresident-xi-jinping-china-economy-society-history-mao-world-chaos-2021-11%5C%22%3EXi%20will%20not%20bend%20on%20his%20vision%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20the%20country.%20He'd%20rather%20shut%20out%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EKnown%20unknowns%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETransparency%20in%20China's%20economic%20data%20has%20always%20moved%20the%20same%20cycles%20as%20its%20politics.%20Now%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-growing-threat-world-economy-stock-market-crash-2022-10%5C%22%3EXi%20and%20the%20CCP%20are%20openly%20embracing%3C%2Fa%3E%20some%20of%20the%20hardline%20practices%20of%20the%20past%2C%20data%20is%20disappearing%20in%20kind.%20The%20most%20worrying%20example%20of%20this%20growing%20secrecy%20comes%20from%20the%20real-estate%20sector.%20China's%20property%20market%20makes%20up%20about%2030%25%20of%20the%20country's%20GDP%2C%20making%20it%20the%20cornerstone%20of%20the%20economy.%20It's%20also%20a%20sector%20where%20crucial%20data%20has%20been%20vanishing%20since%20the%20end%20of%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Statistics%20stopped%20disclosing%20data%20on%20land%20sales%20by%20area%20after%20December%20and%20consumer%20confidence%20after%20March%2C%26quot%3B%20Chu%20and%20her%20colleague%20Fan%20Zhang%20wrote%20in%20a%20recent%20report%20for%20clients.%20%26quot%3BIt%20also%20changed%20how%20it%20calculates%20property%20sales%20and%20investment%20growth%20starting%20in%20March.%26quot%3B%20The%20changes%2C%20Chu%20and%20Zhang%20wrote%2C%20have%20caused%20eyebrow-raising%20gaps%20between%20the%20official%20numbers%20and%20estimates%20based%20on%20an%20aggregate%20of%20secondary%20indicators.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20real%20estate%3A%20Exports%20make%20up%20about%2018%25%20to%2024%25%20of%20China's%20annual%20GDP%2C%20but%20Chu%20wrote%20that%20the%20Chinese%20Custom%20Bureau's%20official%20data%20has%20begun%20to%20diverge%20noticeably%20from%20import%20data%20from%20the%20country's%20trading%20partners.%20Based%20on%20the%20discrepancy%2C%20it's%20becoming%20clear%20that%20China%20is%20overstating%20how%20much%20stuff%20it's%20shipping%20abroad.%20Chu%20said%20she%20now%20uses%20a%20blend%20of%20the%20two%20datasets%2C%20and%20based%20on%20that%20average%20she%20estimates%20that%20China's%202023%20exports%20will%20fall%208%25%20compared%20to%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThe%20authorities%20are%20so%20afraid%20of%20any%20sign%20of%20instability%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20at%20China%20Beige%20Book%2C%20a%20private%20surveyor%20of%20the%20Chinese%20economy%2C%20analysts%20wrote%20that%20official%20numbers%20on%20assets%20firms%20use%20to%20make%20income%20%E2%80%94%20from%20buildings%20to%20bulldozers%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bnow%20border%20on%20useless%26quot%3B%20because%20of%20the%20government's%20constant%20tweaking%20of%20the%20calculations.%20J%20Capital%20Research%2C%20a%20China-focused%20investment%20firm%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20note%20to%20clients%20recently%20that%20key%20proxies%20for%20investment%2C%20such%20as%20the%20amount%20of%20cement%2C%20glass%2C%20and%20tile%20being%20produced%2C%20have%20disappeared%20as%20well.%20These%20are%20numbers%20investors%20used%20to%20figure%20out%20the%20growth%20and%20scale%20of%20China's%20construction%20and%20industrial%20production.%20Not%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWithholding%2Frecalculating%20data%20may%20help%20manage%20confidence%20issues%20domestically%2C%20but%20in%20our%20experience%20it%20can%20undermine%20it%20with%20foreign%20investors%2C%26quot%3B%20Chu%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BSo%20this%20path%20isn't%20costless%2C%20particularly%20with%20foreign%20investor%20and%20multinational%20corporation%20confidence%20also%20low.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForeign%20investors%20have%20been%20taking%20the%20hint%2C%20selling%20Chinese%20domestic%20stocks%20and%20bonds%20at%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fchina-economy-foreign-investors-capital-flows-chinese-stocks-bonds-yuan-2023-8%5C%22%3Erapid%20rate%20for%20the%20past%20few%20weeks%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20Beijing's%20policymakers%20have%20seen%20these%20same%20investors%20get%20the%20jitters%20before%2C%20only%20to%20come%20back%20with%20dollars%20in%20their%20fists%20ready%20to%20pounce%20on%20the%20next%20wave%20of%20growth.%20What%20makes%20this%20time%20different%20is%20that%20without%20accurate%20data%2C%20there's%20no%20way%20to%20tell%20when%20the%20next%20wave%20is%20coming%20%E2%80%94%20so%20there's%20no%20reason%20to%20get%20back%20in%20the%20water%20at%20all.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EUnknown%20Knowns%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESometime%20in%20the%20past%20few%20months%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-2023-predictions-wrong-recession-inflation-stocks-europe-china-2023-1%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20went%20from%20expecting%20that%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20experience%20a%20glorious%20bounce%20back%20from%20COVID%20to%20panicking%20about%20an%20all-out%20economic%20collapse.%20The%20consensus%20from%20those%20calling%20for%20catastrophe%20is%20that%20Xi%20should%20do%20what%20Western%20governments%20did%20during%20the%20pandemic%3A%20send%20checks%20to%20China's%20households%20to%20spur%20consumption%20and%20grease%20the%20wheels%20of%20the%20economy.%20That's%20not%20going%20to%20happen%2C%20even%20though%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-economy-post-covid-rebound-big-bang-stimulus-xi-jinping-2023-8%5C%22%3Eleading%20Chinese%20economists%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20called%20for%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPartially%2C%20this%20is%20about%20politics.%20Xi's%20unwillingness%20to%20send%20out%20stimulus%20checks%20to%20households%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20his%20government's%20disinclination%20to%20let%20go%20of%20that%20control.%20He%20fundamentally%20does%20not%20believe%20average%20people%20should%20direct%20the%20economy%20that%20much.%20A%20recent%20essay%20in%20the%20Study%20Times%2C%20a%20journal%20explaining%20Communist%20Party%20thought%2C%20argued%20that%20sending%20direct%20aid%20to%20families%20would%20not%20only%20be%20expensive%20but%20also%20result%20in%20a%20misallocation%20of%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221838%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Xi%20Jinping%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ea139fbc26b40019907f00%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22919%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20isn't%20going%20to%20suddenly%20change%20his%20mind%20and%20send%20out%20stimulus%20checks%20to%20Chinese%20households.%3Cp%3EXie%20Huanchi%2FXinhua%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%201000%20yuan%20were%20distributed%20to%20each%20person%2C%20it%20would%20require%20about%201.4%20trillion%20yuan%2C%20but%20how%20much%20could%20this%20really%20stimulate%20consumption%3F%20This%20would%20not%20only%20create%20a%20huge%20fiscal%20burden%2C%20but%20residents'%20consumption%20habits%2C%20structures%2C%20and%20willingness%20are%20also%20limiting%20its%20effectiveness%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20essay%20said%2C%20according%20to%20a%20translation%20in%20the%20China-focused%20newsletter%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsinocism.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESinocism%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BEspecially%20since%20the%20pandemic%20has%20to%20some%20extent%20strengthened%20residents'%20precautionary%20motives%2C%20making%20consumption%20more%20conservative%2C%20this%20would%20inevitably%20lead%20to%20inefficient%20use%20of%20valuable%20fiscal%20resources.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReaching%20high-income%20status%20has%20been%20the%20Communist%20Party's%20raison%20d'%C3%AAtre%20for%20decades.%20It's%20why%20the%20government%20joined%20the%20World%20Trade%20Organization%20in%202001%20and%20why%20it%20began%20welcoming%20more%20and%20more%20foreign%20investment%20in%20the%202000s.%20It's%20why%20the%20CCP%20pushed%20the%20debt-to-GDP%20ratio%20to%20almost%20280%25%20to%20fight%20the%202009%20global%20recession.%20And%20it%20is%20why%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-august-economic-data-trends-down-2017-9%5C%22%3Egovernment%20has%20continually%20opened%20the%20credit%20spigots%3C%2Fa%3E%20every%20time%20there%20has%20been%20an%20inkling%20of%20economic%20weakness.%20During%20those%20fracturable%20moments%2C%20state%20banks%20loaned%20money%20mostly%20to%20state-owned%20enterprises%20and%20the%20government%20could%20direct%20the%20process.%20%3Cem%3EThat%3C%2Fem%3E%20process%20led%20to%20an%20inefficient%20allocation%20of%20capital%20that%20kept%20nonperforming%20debt%20in%20the%20financial%20system.%20Victor%20Shih%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20and%20the%20director%20of%20the%2021st%20Century%20China%20Center%20at%20University%20of%20California%20San%20Diego%2C%20told%20me%20that%20it%20would%20take%20payments%20totaling%2010%25%20to%2020%25%20of%20China's%20GDP%20to%20spur%20the%20kind%20of%20consumption%20necessary%20to%20pull%20China%20out%20of%20the%20doldrums%20the%20state%20steered%20it%20into.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20in%20stark%20contrast%20to%20the%20philosophy%20of%20consumer%20empowerment%20practiced%20in%20open%20economies%2C%20where%20individuals%2C%20households%2C%20and%20private%20businesses%20control%20capital.%20If%20money%20is%20power%2C%20then%20handing%20out%20%26quot%3Bhelicopter%20money%26quot%3B%20is%20one%20version%20of%20power%20to%20the%20people.%20Xi%20believes%20power%20belongs%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20state.%20Even%20if%20stimulus%20is%20the%20best%20way%20to%20push%20China's%20economy%20forward%2C%20the%20CCP%20is%20making%20it%20clear%20that%20maintaining%20its%20power%20is%20a%20higher%20priority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20needn't%20pour%20over%20Communist%20Party%20doctrine%20to%20see%20this%20shift%20from%20an%20economy-focused%20government%20to%20a%20power-%20and%20security-focused%20one.%20The%20signs%20are%20everywhere%3A%20in%20the%20crackdown%20on%20private-sector%20businesses%2C%20in%20the%20all-too-normal%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Fjack-ma-isnt-back%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisappearances%20of%20high-profile%20billionaires%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20in%20Beijing's%20new%20anti-espionage%20law%20that%20some%20analysts%20worry%20will%20turn%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeignpolicy.com%2F2023%2F08%2F17%2Fchina-foreign-business-risks-political-prisoners%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregular%20financial%20due%20diligence%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20a%20crime.%20Over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20foreign%20consulting%20firms%20have%20been%20raided%20by%20the%20authorities%2C%20and%20the%20Ministry%20of%20State%20Security%20%E2%80%94%20once%20a%20shadowy%20organization%20%E2%80%94%20has%20developed%20a%20presence%20on%20WeChat%20where%20citizens%20are%20encouraged%20to%20report%20any%20behavior%20that%20could%20be%20deemed%20anti-party.%20In%20this%20environment%2C%20the%20risk%20for%20foreigners%20isn't%20just%20that%20they%20break%20a%20law%2C%20it's%20that%20they%20don't%20know%20that%20they're%20breaking%20a%20law%20while%20they're%20breaking%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EUnknown%20Unknowns%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20keeping%20everyone%20in%20the%20dark%20about%20the%20economy%2C%20Beijing%20may%20think%20that%20it%20is%20reclaiming%20power%20and%20mitigating%20social%20instability.%20What%20it's%20really%20doing%20is%20showing%20its%20hand.%20State%20mouthpieces%20can%20continue%20to%20give%20lip%20service%20to%20opening%20and%20reform%2C%20but%20Beijing's%20actions%20show%20that%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party's%20priorities%20have%20shifted%20from%20economic%20development%20to%20maintaining%20a%20closed%20society%20where%20it%20is%20absolutely%20dominant.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBasically%2C%20the%20authorities%20are%20so%20afraid%20of%20any%20sign%20of%20instability%2C%26quot%3B%20Shih%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20believe%20the%20financial%20system%20to%20be%20so%20fragile%2C%20they%20fear%20any%20shock%20could%20cause%20a%20crisis.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20part%20because%20of%20that%20fear%2C%20policymakers%20handle%20economic%20problems%20piecemeal%20%E2%80%94%20in%20order%20of%20most%20glaring%20first%20%E2%80%94%20without%20allowing%20for%20an%20overall%20correction%20in%20sectors%20that%20are%20failing%2C%20such%20as%20property.%20Over%20time%2C%20this%20only%20exacerbates%20debt%20problems%20and%20adds%20volatility%20to%20the%20system.%20While%20Beijing%20plays%20financial%20meltdown%20whack-a-mole%2C%20investors%20need%20to%20calculate%20risk.%20Without%20data%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20know%20where%20the%20Chinese%20economy%20is%20going%2C%20but%20through%20the%20blur%2C%20investors%20can%20see%20a%20trajectory%20led%20by%20the%20CCP's%20ideological%20framework%20and%20weighed%20down%20by%20debt.%20In%20this%20scenario%2C%20it%20ultimately%20becomes%20harder%2C%20not%20easier%2C%20to%20know%20what's%20going%20on.%20And%20Xi's%20fine%20with%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Flinette-lopez%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%223d07cb941339da2e21063cb719e18b0c%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Flinette-lopez%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3ELinette%20Lopez%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-hiding-bad-data-economy-debt-real-estate-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693301161000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e906e4b413420019a3c80a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-hiding-bad-data-economy-debt-real-estate-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20and%20the%20Chinese%20government%20have%20a%20brilliant%20plan%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20country's%20economic%20turmoil%3A%20hide%20how%20bad%20it%20is.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22llopez%40insider.com%20(Linette%20Lopez)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A53%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-hiding-bad-data-economy-debt-real-estate-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Article%2035A%20Returned%20To%20Spotlight%20In%20Supreme%20Court's%20J%26amp%3BK%20Hearing%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20ongoing%20hearing%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20centre's%202019%20decision%20to%20strip%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20of%20its%20special%20status%20has%20brought%20Article%2035A%20of%20the%20Constitution%20back%20into%20the%20spotlight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20was%20Article%2035A%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%2035A%20empowered%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir's%20legislature%20to%20decide%20who%20the%20erstwhile%20state's%20permanent%20residents%20were%20and%20to%20extend%20special%20rights%20and%20privileges%20to%20them.%20This%20was%20added%20to%20the%20Constitution%20in%201954%20by%20a%20presidential%20order%20issued%20under%20Article%20370.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20were%20J%26amp%3BK's%20Permanent%20Residents%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPermanent%20residents%20were%20defined%20as%20those%20who%20lived%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20when%20the%20law%20was%20approved%20in%201954%20or%20those%20who%20lived%20there%20for%2010%20consecutive%20years%20after%20that%20and%20own%20property%20there.%20Permanent%20Residents%20received%20a%20certificate%20s%20proof.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Article%2035A%20Changed%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20Article%20barred%20outsiders%20from%20owning%20property%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20It%20also%20made%20them%20ineligible%20for%20government%20jobs%20or%20scholarships%20in%20state-run%20educational%20institution.%20Under%20the%20Article%2C%20women%20who%20married%20non-residents%20did%20not%20have%20the%20right%20to%20own%20property%20--%20this%20changed%20after%20a%202002%20court%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Changed%20In%202019%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20centre%20revoked%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir's%20special%20status%20and%20bifurcated%20it%20into%20two%20Union%20Territories%20in%202019%2C%20a%20new%20Presidential%20order%20was%20issued%20that%20applied%20all%20provisions%20of%20the%20Constitution%20to%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20residents.%20In%20effect%2C%20this%20meant%20that%20the%20privileges%20enjoyed%20by%20Permanent%20Residents%20under%20Article%2035A%20became%20inoperative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChief%20Justice's%20Big%20Remark%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%2035A%2C%20now%20defunct%2C%20resurfaced%20during%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20hearing%20on%20Article%20370.%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20said%20in%20a%20strong%20remark%20yesterday%20that%20this%20provision%20had%20deprived%20people%20not%20residing%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20of%20some%20key%20constitutional%20rights.%20Equality%20of%20opportunity%2C%20employment%20in%20the%20state%20government%20and%20right%20to%20buy%20land%20--%20%26quot%3Ball%20this%20article%20snatches%20away%20from%20citizens...%20Because%20the%20residents%20(of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir)%20had%20special%20rights%2C%20the%20non-residents%20were%20excluded%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693301160000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2F4qgfvaco_supreme-court-new_625x300_11_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farticle-35a-article-370-jammu-and-kashmir-supreme-court-how-article-35a-returned-to-spotlight-in-supreme-courts-j-k-hearing-4338962%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20ongoing%20hearing%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20centre's%202019%20decision%20to%20strip%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20of%20its%20special%20status%20has%20brought%20Article%2035A%20of%20the%20Constitution%20back%20into%20the%20spotlight.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farticle-35a-article-370-jammu-and-kashmir-supreme-court-how-article-35a-returned-to-spotlight-in-supreme-courts-j-k-hearing-4338962%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farticle-35a-article-370-jammu-and-kashmir-supreme-court-how-article-35a-returned-to-spotlight-in-supreme-courts-j-k-hearing-4338962%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farticle-35a-article-370-jammu-and-kashmir-supreme-court-how-article-35a-returned-to-spotlight-in-supreme-courts-j-k-hearing-4338962%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22On%20J%26amp%3BK%20Statehood%20Timeframe%2C%20Centre%20To%20Inform%20Supreme%20Court%20On%20Thursday%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20will%20on%20Thursday%20make%20a%20%26quot%3Bpositive%20statement%26quot%3B%20on%20restoration%20of%20statehood%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2Fjammu-and-kashmir%5C%22%3EJammu%20and%20Kashmir%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20told%20today%20after%20it%20asked%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Btimeframe%26quot%3B%20for%20such%20a%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20-%20hearing%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20scrapping%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2Farticle-370%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArticle%20370%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20gave%20J%26amp%3BK%20its%20special%20status%20-%20had%20stressed%20the%20need%20for%20restoration%20of%20democracy%20as%20it%20asked%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%2C%20%26quot%3BCan%20you%20convert%20a%20State%20into%20a%20UT%3F%20Can%20a%20UT%20be%20carved%20out%20of%20a%20State%3F%26quot%3B%20and%20when%20elections%20could%20be%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20has%20to%20come%20an%20end...%20give%20us%20the%20specific%20time%20frame%20as%20to%20when%20will%20you%20restore%20actual%20democracy.%20We%20want%20to%20record%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20this%20Mr%20Mehta%20had%20replied%20in%20the%20affirmative%20and%20pointed%20to%20Assam%2C%20Tripura%20and%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20as%20examples.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20taken%20instructions.%20The%20instructions%20are%20that%20'union%20territory'%20is%20not%20a%20permanent%20feature...%20I%20will%20make%20a%20positive%20statement%20day%20after%20tomorrow.%20Ladakh%20will%20remain%20a%20UT%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Mehta%20said%20as%20he%20read%20out%20statements%20on%20the%20status%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20made%20by%20Union%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Constitution%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20which%20is%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%2C%20also%20acknowledged%20national%20security%20concerns%20-%20posited%20by%20the%20government%20when%20Article%20370%20was%20scrapped%20four%20years%20ago%20-%20but%20reminded%20the%20latter%20of%20the%20importance%20of%20bringing%20back%20democracy%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20%7C%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farticle-35a-robbed-non-residents-of-j-k-of-fundamental-rights-dy-chandrachud-4337690%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArticle%2035A%20Denied%20J%26amp%3BK%20Non-Residents%20Their%20Key%20Rights%3A%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202019%20the%20government%20-%20amid%20a%20furious%20pushback%20from%20political%20activists%20and%20opposition%20leaders%20-%20scrapped%20Article%20370%20and%20split%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20into%20two%20union%20territories%20-%20J%26amp%3BK%20and%20Ladakh.%20The%20government%20had%20assured%20its%20critics%20that%20statehood%20would%20restored%20%26quot%3Bonce%20situation%20returns%20to%20normal%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20statement%20(on%20restoration%20of%20statehood)%20has%20been%20made%20on%20Parliament%20floor.%20Efforts%20are%20being%20made...%20once%20situation%20returns%20to%20normal%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Mehta%20told%20the%20court%20today%2C%20the%2012th%20