%3D%5C%22999%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChris%20Williams.%3Cp%3EChris%20Williams%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EChris%20Williams%20is%20a%20former%20Microsoft%20VP%20of%20HR%20and%20a%20podcaster%2C%20consultant%2C%20and%20TikTok%20creator.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20writes%20that%20bad%20managers%20are%20often%20self-centered%20and%20overly%20focused%20on%20their%20image.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWilliams%20also%20says%20that%20bad%20managers%20are%20so%20afraid%20of%20failure%20that%20their%20teams%20bury%20any%20evidence%20of%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20seen%20more%20than%20a%20few%20bad%20managers%20in%20my%20over%2040%20years%20of%20business%2C%20leadership%2C%20and%20consulting%20%E2%80%94%20including%20as%20the%20Vice%20President%20of%20HR%20at%20Microsoft.%20Here%20are%20four%20traits%20I've%20seen%20in%20almost%20every%20one%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Self-centered%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20common%20trait%20I've%20seen%20in%20bad%20managers%20is%20a%20relentless%20focus%20on%20themselves.%20Everything%20is%20all%20about%20them.%20Whether%20it's%20driven%20by%20ego%20or%20panic%2C%20bad%20managers%20are%20always%20worried%20about%20how%20they%20appear%20to%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBad%20managers%20stress%20about%20how%20they%20look%20to%20their%20boss.%20Do%20I%20look%20strong%20or%20weak%3F%20Do%20they%20think%20I'm%20an%20idiot%3F%20How%20do%20my%20peers%20see%20me%3F%20What%20about%20those%20above%20my%20boss%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBad%20managers%20fret%20about%20what%20their%20team%20thinks%20of%20them.%20They%20want%20desperately%20to%20be%20looked%20up%20to.%20They%20must%20have%20all%20the%20answers.%20Rather%20than%20focus%20on%20issues%2C%20it's%20all%20about%20appearances.%20They%20want%20to%20appear%20strong%2C%20unflappable%2C%20even%20invincible%20to%20their%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20managers%20do%20this%20out%20of%20ego.%20They%20need%20to%20be%20the%20center%20of%20attention%2C%20the%20focus%20of%20their%20world.%20They%20want%20everything%20in%20their%20team%20to%20be%20for%20their%20benefit.%20Perhaps%20to%20enhance%20their%20career.%20More%20often%20to%20stoke%20their%20ego.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20egotists%20are%20the%20exception%2C%20not%20the%20rule.%20More%20common%20are%20the%20worriers.%20The%20nervous%20managers%20cowering%20under%20the%20weight%20of%20their%20own%20imposter%20syndrome.%20Afraid%20of%20being%20exposed%2C%20they%20put%20on%20the%20bravest%20of%20faces.%20Worried%20what%20others%20must%20think%20of%20them.%20Not%20realizing%20how%20rarely%20others%20ever%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFailing%20to%20see%20that%20it's%20the%20results%20that%20count%2C%20they%20worry%20about%20image.%20Their%20image.%20So%2C%20they%20try%20to%20control%20every%20aspect%20of%20their%20presentation%20to%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20working%20with%20their%20team%20to%20create%20the%20results%20that%20would%20get%20them%20notice%2C%20they%20make%20it%20all%20about%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Input%20focused%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20bad%20managers%20are%20inordinately%20focused%20on%20the%20inputs%20to%20their%20processes%2C%20not%20the%20output%20results%20of%20the%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20stress%20about%20employees%20who%20are%20two%20minutes%20late%20or%20too%20often%20in%20the%20restroom.%20They%20track%20their%20employees'%20every%20move%2C%20their%20every%20keystroke.%20They%20worry%20about%20hours%20input%2C%20not%20results%20output.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20obsession%20with%20image%20spills%20out%20here%20as%20well.%20They%20stress%20about%20professional%20appearance%2C%20not%20professional%20results.%20They%20want%20everyone%20to%20always%20at%20least%20look%20busy.%20There's%20no%20greater%20crime%20than%20a%20happy%20employee%20enjoying%20their%20time%20with%20their%20co-workers.%20It's%20all%20business%2C%20all%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20managers%20relentlessly%20track%20everything%2C%20all%20the%20wrong%20things.%20They%20track%20time%20spent%20with%20the%20customer%2C%20not%20whether%20the%20customer%20was%20satisfied.%20They%20track%20keystrokes%20per%20minute%2C%20not%20problems%20resolved.%20They%20monitor%20employees%20as%20if%20they%20were%20robots%2C%20looking%20for%20the%20slightest%20variation%20from%20their%20ideal%20automaton.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20managers%20lose%20sight%20of%20the%20forest%20for%20the%20trees.%20Instead%20of%20being%20obsessed%20with%20results%2C%20sales%2C%20and%20happy%20customers%2C%20they%20are%20focused%20on%20the%20inputs%20%E2%80%94%20the%20inputs%20that%20feel%20easier%20to%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Afraid%20of%20failure%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spin%20off%20from%20the%20obsession%20with%20image%2C%20these%20bad%20managers%20are%20deeply%20afraid%20of%20failure.%20Particularly%20any%20appearance%20of%20failure%20that%20might%20reflect%20poorly%20on%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20embracing%20the%20odd%20failure%20as%20the%20inevitable%20consequence%20of%20a%20team%20that's%20pushing%20the%20boundaries%2C%20these%20managers%20are%20obsessed%20with%20perfection.%20Instead%20of%20searching%20for%20causes%2C%20they%20hunt%20for%20someone%20to%20blame.%20Rather%20than%20finding%20a%20chance%20for%20all%20to%20learn%2C%20they%20see%20a%20reason%20to%20be%20embarrassed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOutwardly%2C%20they%20bury%20any%20evidence%20of%20a%20misstep%2C%20hoping%20it%20never%20sees%20the%20light%20of%20day.%20Worried%20it%20will%20reflect%20badly%20on%20their%20record%2C%20they%20find%20excuses%20or%20culprits.%20Anywhere%20else%20to%20cast%20the%20negative%20light.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20the%20team%20becomes%20trained%20to%20also%20bury%20any%20evidence%20of%20failure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResults%20are%20even%20falsified%20to%20prevent%20disclosure%20of%20any%20outcome%20that%20falls%20short%20of%20perfection.%20Just%20like%20their%20manager%2C%20they%20grow%20averse%20to%20failure.%20The%20better%20to%20avoid%20the%20harsh%20consequences%20of%20discovery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20becomes%20tentative%2C%20careful%20in%20every%20step.%20No%20risks%20are%20taken%2C%20and%20no%20boundaries%20are%20even%20approached%2C%20lest%20the%20result%20be%20the%20smallest%20failing.%20Safe%20and%20cautious%20to%20the%20point%20of%20being%20timid%2C%20the%20team%20underperforms.%20Only%20to%20earn%20the%20further%20ire%20of%20the%20perfectionist%20in%20chief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20push%20the%20team%20the%20bad%20manager%20plays%20everything%20safe.%20Rather%20than%20learn%20from%2C%20even%20embrace%2C%20failure%2C%20they%20lash%20out%20and%20bury%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Information%20hoarder%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20leads%20to%20a%20manager%20who%20treats%20information%20as%20a%20precious%20commodity%20to%20be%20hoarded%20%E2%80%94%20rather%20than%20a%20gift%20to%20be%20shared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bad%20manager%20controls%20the%20narrative%20both%20into%20and%20out%20of%20the%20team.%20They%20maintain%20strict%20control%20over%20communication%20outside%20the%20team.%20They%20monitor%20email%20and%20meetings%2C%20insisting%20on%20being%20copied%20or%20included.%20They%20meticulously%20review%20and%20edit%20every%20scrap%20of%20information%20that%20might%20find%20its%20way%20to%20the%20higher-ups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfraid%20of%20upsetting%20the%20team%2C%20the%20bad%20manager%20hides%20bad%20news%20they%20learn%20from%20above%20or%20around%20them.%20They%20portray%20it%20as%20heroically%20shielding%20the%20team%20from%20the%20noise.%20In%20reality%2C%20they%20are%20postponing%20the%20inevitable%20discovery%20through%20other%20sources.%20Without%20control%20of%20the%20news%2C%20the%20manager%20only%20looks%20worse%2C%20their%20greatest%20fear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20manager%20and%20the%20team%20soon%20find%20themselves%20lying%20to%20each%20other.%20And%20to%20everyone%20outside.%20%26quot%3BEverything's%20great%20here%3B%20no%20need%20to%20worry%20about%20us.%26quot%3B%20Even%20as%20the%20fires%20of%20doom%20burn%20ever%20closer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETeams%20run%20by%20bad%20managers%20often%20resemble%20cults%20in%20this%20way.%20They%20become%20isolated%20islands%20cut%20off%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20organization.%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20tell%20you%2C%20that's%20need%20to%20know%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Byou%20wouldn't%20understand%26quot%3B%20are%20common%20refrains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20teams%20rarely%20outperform%2C%20but%20you'd%20never%20know%20that%20from%20the%20limited%20available%20information%20%E2%80%94%20information%20hoarded%20jealously%20by%20their%20bad%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EManagers%20like%20this%20are%20famous%20%E2%80%94%20for%20the%20wrong%20reasons%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20this%20array%20of%20common%20traits%2C%20bad%20managers%20often%20become%20famous%20within%20the%20organization.%20But%20not%20in%20the%20way%20they%20would%20hope.%20They%20are%20looked%20on%20with%20disdain%2C%20even%20pity%2C%20from%20the%20outside.%20Smart%20employees%20warn%20their%20peers%20to%20avoid%20them.%20Refugees%20from%20the%20team%20tell%20stories%20far%20and%20wide.%20Many%20simply%20quit%20to%20escape%20the%20pain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20most%20frustrating%2C%20the%20manager%20endures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20even%20ramp%20up%20their%20tactics.%20Their%20carefully%20masked%20image%20of%20success%20hides%20them%20from%20consequences.%20The%20organization%20suffers%2C%20often%20rewarding%20the%20behavior%20that%20makes%20them%20such%20bad%20managers%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20Like%20cockroaches%20in%20the%20end%20times%2C%20bad%20managers%20find%20a%20way%20to%20endure.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.clwill.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EChris%20Williams%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20former%20vice%20president%20of%20HR%20at%20Microsoft%20and%20a%20leadership%20advisor%2C%20podcaster%2C%20TikTok%20creator%2C%20a