nd%20soap%20that%20need%20to%20be%20refilled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20come%20across%20rooms%20with%20vomit%2C%20beds%20with%20blood%20on%20them%2C%20and%20bathrooms%20where%20someone%20has%20left%20feces%20in%20the%20bathtub.%20I've%20also%20had%20to%20clean%20rooms%20with%20a%20really%20strong%20odor%20left%20over%20from%20marijuana%20or%20cigars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20more-annoying%20tasks%20is%20cleaning%20up%20overflowing%20trash.%20Sometimes%20guests%20leave%20behind%20tons%20of%20bottles%20and%20takeout%20containers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDogs%20can%20also%20be%20difficult.%20I%20adore%20dogs%2C%20but%20sometimes%20they%20leave%20so%20much%20fur%20behind%20that%20we%20have%20to%20shampoo%20the%20carpets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20one%20leaves%20tips%20anymore%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20began%20working%20at%20the%20hotel%2C%20guests%20would%20leave%20tips%2C%20but%20now%20most%20people%20don't%20leave%20anything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20first%20years%20as%20a%20housekeeper%2C%20I%20could%20expect%20to%20make%20%241%2C500%20to%20%242%2C000%20a%20year%20in%20tips.%20It%20slowly%20got%20lower%20to%20maybe%20%24200%20or%20%24300%20a%20year.%20This%20is%20the%20lowest%20year%20yet%2C%20and%20I'm%20getting%20almost%20nothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20staying%20in%20a%20hotel%2C%20I%20suggest%20leaving%20a%20tip%20of%20%245%20to%20%2410%20a%20night.%20Don't%20wait%20until%20the%20end%20of%20the%20stay%20because%20a%20different%20housekeeper%20may%20clean%20your%20room%20each%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUncertainty%20about%20getting%20called%20in%20makes%20life%20hard%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELately%2C%20I've%20been%20working%20less%20because%20there%20are%20fewer%20rooms%20to%20clean.%20I%20get%20fewer%20hours%20of%20work%20and%20earn%20a%20lower%20income.%20If%20the%20guests%20opt%20out%20of%20the%20housekeeping%20service%2C%20and%20their%20room%20isn't%20cleaned%20for%20two%20or%20three%20days%2C%20that%20means%20less%20work%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20those%20days%2C%20the%20hotel%20might%20not%20call%20me%20in%20to%20work.%20It%20affects%20me%20economically%20to%20have%20my%20paycheck%20go%20up%20and%20down%20like%20that%20because%20I%20have%20to%20pay%20rent%2C%20buy%20food%2C%20and%20cover%20transportation.%20I%20also%20support%20my%2090-year-old%20mom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20weeks%20ago%2C%20I%20worked%20only%20one%20day%20the%20whole%20week%2C%20and%20on%20the%20other%20days%2C%20I%20was%20on%20call%20waiting%20to%20see%20whether%20there%20would%20be%20work%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20good%20week%2C%20I'm%20bringing%20in%20%24850.%20But%20on%20a%20week%20when%20I'm%20called%20in%20for%20only%20a%20few%20days%20of%20work%2C%20I%20make%20about%20%24500.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20encourage%20hotel%20guests%20to%20get%20daily%20housekeeping%20because%20you%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20power%20to%20help%20us%20go%20to%20work%20and%20make%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETry%20not%20to%20leave%20the%20room%20too%20messy%20if%20you're%20staying%20at%20a%20hotel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20will%20make%20your%20housekeeper's%20life%20easier%20if%20you%20don't%20leave%20a%20big%20mess.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20sometimes%20don't%20think%20about%20how%20they'll%20affect%20my%20ability%20to%20do%20my%20job%2C%20and%20they%20leave%20clothes%20or%20suitcases%20on%20top%20of%20the%20bed%20that%20I%20need%20to%20make.%20Or%20they%20leave%20heavy%20things%2C%20such%20as%20a%20luggage%20rack%20full%20of%20bags%2C%20in%20the%20way%2C%20and%20I%20need%20to%20move%20it%20to%20clean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20painful%20thing%20for%20me%20is%20how%20often%20I%20need%20to%20bend%20down.%20Guests%20can%20help%20with%20that%20a%20lot%2C%20too.%20You%20can%20leave%20the%20towels%20in%20a%20single%20pile%20so%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20bend%20over%20many%20times%20to%20pick%20them%20up%20one%20by%20one.%20You%20can%20also%20put%20all%20the%20trash%20in%20the%20trash%20cans%20so%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20go%20around%20the%20room%20and%20bend%20over%20many%20times%20to%20pick%20things%20up%20off%20the%20floor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHonestly%2C%20I%20love%20my%20job%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20sometimes%20ask%20why%20I%20don't%20change%20jobs%2C%20but%20I%20like%20it.%20I%20sincerely%20like%20this%20job%20better%20than%20my%20former%20job%20as%20a%20secretary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20it%20when%20I%20feel%20like%20I've%20made%20someone%20happy%20by%20giving%20them%20a%20clean%20room.%20When%20a%20guest%20stops%20me%20in%20the%20hallway%20to%20thank%20me%20and%20tell%20me%20what%20a%20difference%20I%20made%20for%20their%20trip%2C%20there's%20nothing%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20housekeeper%20who%20wants%20to%20share%20your%20story%3F%20Email%20Lauryn%20Haas%20at%20lhaas%40insider.com.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousekeeper-hotel-san-francisco-shares-what-its-like-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693299781000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ecc184ecb92e00192543c9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousekeeper-hotel-san-francisco-shares-what-its-like-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Marriott%20housekeeper%20suggests%20that%20hotel%20guests%20leave%20a%20%245%20to%20%2410%20tip%20every%20night%2C%20put%20used%20towels%20in%20one%20pile%2C%20and%20respect%20the%20space.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Elle%20Hardy)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousekeeper-hotel-san-francisco-shares-what-its-like-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chanel's%20CEO%20says%20she's%20been%20the%20'first%20woman%2C%20the%20first%20brown%20person%2C%20the%20first%20Asian%2C%20the%20fir