alUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fasia-cup%2Fasia-cup-2023-kl-rahul-unavailable-for-first-two-games-says-team-india-coach-rahul-dravid%2Farticleshow%2F103166859.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Article%20370%20Hearings%3A%20Article%2035A%20Comes%20Under%20Critical%20Scrutiny%20Before%20Supreme%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F17134928%2FSupreme_Court_of_India_01-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EChief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20heading%20the%20five-Judge%20Constitution%20Bench%20hearing%20the%20slew%20of%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20on%20Monday%20(August%2028)%20observed%20that%20Article%2035A%20while%20giving%20special%20rights%20to%20permanent%20residents%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20denied%20fundamental%20rights%20to%20others.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%9CArticle%2035A%20gave%20special%20rights%20and%20privileges%20to%20permanent%20residents%20and%20virtually%20took%20away%20the%20rights%20of%20non-residents.%20These%20rights%20included%20the%20right%20to%20equal%20opportunity%20of%20state%20employment%2C%20right%20to%20acquire%20property%20and%20the%20right%20to%20settle%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20CJI%20remarked%20while%20intervening%20during%20the%20submission%20of%20solicitor%20general%2C%20Tushar%20Mehta.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EArticle%2035A%20of%20the%20constitution%20was%20inserted%20in%201954%20by%20a%20presidential%20order%20made%20under%20Article%20370%20of%20the%20constitution.%20Article%2035A%20enabled%20the%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir%20Assembly%20to%20define%20%E2%80%98permanent%20residents%E2%80%99%20and%20allowed%20it%20to%20give%20Permanent%20Resident%20Certificates%20to%20people%20in%20the%20state.%20The%20permanent%20residents%20enjoyed%20special%20rights%20and%20privileges%20in%20regard%20to%20employment%2C%20acquisition%20of%20immovable%20property%2C%20settlements%20and%20scholarships%2C%20until%20Article%20370%20was%20read%20down%20on%20August%205%2C%202019.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20CJI%20also%20noted%20that%20Article%2035A%20had%20even%20granted%20immunity%20from%20judicial%20review%20to%20these%20special%20privileges.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20response%20to%20the%20CJI%E2%80%99s%20remark%20that%20the%20current%20Union%20government%20cannot%20distance%20itself%20from%20its%20predecessors%2C%20Mehta%20answered%20that%20the%20August%205%2C%202019%20decision%20was%20an%20attempt%20to%20correct%20the%20mistakes%20of%20the%20predecessor%20governments.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20mistakes%20of%20the%20past%20should%20not%20befall%20the%20future%20generations%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20responded.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMehta%20told%20the%20Bench%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esafai%20karamcharis%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(sanitation%20workers)%20brought%20to%20J%26amp%3BK%20were%20not%20entitled%20to%20permanent%20resident%20status%20despite%20residing%20in%20the%20state%20for%20several%20decades.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fday-10-of-article-370-hearing-union-govt-says-jks-accession-was-not-unique%5C%22%3EDay%2010%20of%20Article%20370%20Hearing%3A%20Union%20Govt%20Says%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20Accession%20Was%20Not%20Unique%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20senior%20counsel%20Kapil%20Sibal%20referred%20to%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20defence%20of%20restrictions%20on%20outsiders%2C%20Mehta%20suggested%20that%20it%20was%20a%20mistake%2C%20due%20to%20which%20the%20state%20was%20deprived%20of%20investments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20also%20highlighted%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20claims%20that%20post-August%205%2C%202019%2C%20there%20has%20been%20an%20upswing%20in%20investments%20and%20tourism.%20He%20claimed%20that%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%20%E2%80%93%20being%20challenged%20in%20the%20petitions%20before%20the%20Court%20%E2%80%93%20confers%20fundamental%20rights%20on%20the%20people%20in%20the%20state%20by%20applying%20the%20entire%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%20bringing%20them%20at%20par.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMehta%20claimed%20that%20it%20is%20not%20unusual%20for%20the%20parliament%20to%20act%20as%20the%20state%20legislative%20assembly%20during%20the%20President%E2%80%99s%20rule.%20parliament%20exercises%20the%20power%20of%20the%20state%20legislature%20under%20Article%20356(1)(b)%20in%20all%20states%2C%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMehta%20also%20contended%20that%20the%20Proviso%20to%20Article%203%20of%20the%20constitution%20%E2%80%93%20dealing%20with%20formation%20of%20new%20states%20and%20alteration%20of%20areas%2C%20boundaries%20or%20names%20of%20existing%20states%20%E2%80%93%20remains%20suspended%20under%20every%20instance%20of%20imposition%20of%20President%E2%80%99s%20rule.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Proviso%20states%20that%20no%20Bill%20for%20this%20purpose%20can%20be%20introduced%20in%20the%20parliament%20except%20if%20the%20President%20recommends%20it.%20Additionally%2C%20if%20the%20Bill%20proposes%20a%20change%20in%20the%20area%2C%20boundaries%20or%20name%20of%20any%20of%20the%20states%2C%20it%20should%20be%20referred%20to%20the%20state%20legislature%20for%20due%20consideration.%20The%20legislature%20would%20then%20be%20allowed%20to%20respond%20within%20the%20period%2C%20stipulated%20by%20the%20President%20or%20in%20the%20reference%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-asks-ag-to-look-into-suspension-of-jk-lecturer-after-his-appearance-in-article-370-hearing%5C%22%3ESC%20Asks%20AG%20to%20Look%20Into%20Suspension%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20Lecturer%20After%20His%20Appearance%20in%20Article%20370%20Hearing%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20CJI%20disagreed%20with%20Mehta%20when%20the%20latter%20sought%20to%20equate%20the%20views%20expressed%20by%20individual%20members%20of%20parliament%20describing%20Article%20370%20as%20a%20temporary%20provision%20with%20that%20of%20parliament%20as%20a%20collective%20body.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMehta%20contended%20that%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Constituent%20Assembly%20was%20not%20a%20law%20making%20body%2C%20and%20the%20state%20Constitution%20was%20not%20a%20document%20of%20governance.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20bench%20took%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-asks-ag-to-look-into-suspension-of-jk-lecturer-after-his-appearance-in-article-370-hearing%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eserious%20objection%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkashmiri-lecturer-suspended-after-appearing-in-supreme-court-for-article-370-hearing%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esuspension%20of%20lecturer%20Zahoor%20Ahmad%20Bhat%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20subsequent%20to%20his%20appearance%20before%20the%20Bench%20in%20the%20ongoing%20proceedings%2C%20by%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Education%20Department.%20Bhat%20had%20appeared%20as%20a%20party-in-person%20on%20August%2024%2C%20and%20shared%20his%20concerns%20over%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370.%20He%20claimed%20that%20he%20found%20it%20difficult%20to%20teach%20the%20principles%20of%20Indian%20constitution%20and%20democracy%20to%20students%2C%20as%20students%20ask%20him%20whether%20India%20is%20still%20a%20democracy%20after%20the%20abrogation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-asks-ag-to-look-into-suspension-of-jk-lecturer-after-his-appearance-in-article-370-hearing%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMehta%20initially%20sought%20to%20justify%20the%20suspension%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20saying%20there%20were%20other%20issues%20like%20his%20appearance%20in%20various%20courts%2C%20the%20bench%20queried%20him%20why%20the%20order%20of%20suspension%20mentioned%20his%20appearance%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20and%20why%20he%20was%20not%20suspended%20earlier%2C%20if%20there%20were%20valid%20reasons.%20Following%20the%20bench%E2%80%99s%20request%20to%20the%20Attorney%20General%2C%20R.%20Venkatramani%20to%20look%20into%20it%2C%20Mehta%20agreed%20with%20the%20bench%20that%20suspension%20cannot%20be%20resorted%20to%20as%20a%20retribution%2C%20and%20the%20timing%20of%20suspension%20is%20indeed%20not%20proper.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693296414000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F17134928%2FSupreme_Court_of_India_01-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Farticle-370-hearings-article-35a-comes-under-critical-scrutiny-before-supreme-court%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Both%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20CJI%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20appeared%20to%20agree%20on%20the%20perceived%20discriminatory%20nature%20of%20Article%2035A%20of%20the%20Constitution.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Farticle-370-hearings-article-35a-comes-under-critical-scrutiny-before-supreme-court%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Maruti%20Suzuki%20plans%20to%20double%20production%20capacity%20to%204%20mn%20over%208%20years%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693296374000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Fa