%9D%20is%20placed%20east%20of%20Taiwan%2C%20underlining%20Beijing%E2%80%99s%20claims%20over%20the%20island%2C%E2%80%99%20the%20report%20says%2C%20of%20the%20map%20released%20by%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20Ministry%20of%20Natural%20Resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20government-owned%20English%20news%20portal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chinadaily.com.cn%2Fa%2F202308%2F28%2FWS64ec91c2a31035260b81ea5b.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EChinaDaily%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20quoted%20Wu%20Wenzhong%2C%20chief%20planner%20of%20the%20ministry%2C%20as%20having%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Csurveying%2C%20mapping%20and%20geographic%20information%20play%20an%20important%20role%20in%20boosting%20the%20development%20of%20the%20nation%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20sources%2C%20China%20undertakes%20this%20exercise%20every%20year.%20But%2C%20it%20is%20not%20always%20made%20public.%20The%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20details%20were%20disseminated%2C%20starting%20with%20the%20%3Cem%3EGlobal%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20sharing%20it%20in%20English%2C%20gave%20the%20distinct%20impression%20that%20it%20was%20a%20signal%20for%20India%20prior%20to%20the%20G-20%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20move%20from%20China%20was%20announced%20after%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-raised-border-stand-off-issue-in-conversation-with-xi-at-brics-says-foreign-secretary%5C%22%3Erecent%20encounter%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20BRICS%20summit.%20The%20differing%20readouts%20from%20the%20two%20sides%20indicated%20that%20there%20was%20no%20change%20in%20the%20position%20on%20the%20resolution%20of%20the%20border%20stand-off%20at%20eastern%20Ladakh%20which%20began%20in%20April-May%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20external%20affairs%20ministry%20has%20not%20yet%20reacted%20to%20the%20latest%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-artid%3D%5C%2267245869%5C%22%20data-title%3D%5C%22China%20releases%20new%20official%20map%2C%20showing%20territorial%20claims%5C%22%20data-url%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Finternational%2Fchina-releases-new-official-map-showing-territorial-claims%2Farticle67245869.ece%5C%22%3EIn%20April%20this%20year%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Ffor-the-third-time-china-renames-places-in-arunachal-pradesh%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20how%20China%E2%80%99s%20Ministry%20of%20Civil%20Affairs%20released%20the%20%E2%80%9Cstandardised%E2%80%9D%20names%20for%2011%20places%20in%20%E2%80%9CZangnam%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20is%20Chinese%20nomenclature%20for%20Arunachal%20Pradesh.%20This%20was%20the%20third%20time%20in%20six%20years%20that%20China%20has%20announced%20Chinese%20names%20for%20geographical%20features%20in%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%2C%20reiterating%20its%20claim%20to%20the%20entire%20Indian%20state.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-artid%3D%5C%2267245869%5C%22%20data-title%3D%5C%22China%20releases%20new%20official%20map%2C%20showing%20territorial%20claims%5C%22%20data-url%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Finternational%2Fchina-releases-new-official-map-showing-territorial-claims%2Farticle67245869.ece%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20had%20then%20rejected%20the%20move%20%E2%80%9Coutright%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReacting%20to%20China%E2%80%99s%20latest%20assertion%2C%20Congress%20president%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20said%20that%C2%A0Arunachal%20Pradesh%20and%20Aksai%20Chin%20are%20%E2%80%9Can%20indistinguishable%20and%20inalienable%20part%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20no%20%E2%80%9Carbitrarily%20invented%20Chinese%20map%20can%20change%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CChina%20is%20a%20habitual%20offender%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20renaming%20and%20redrawing%20maps%20of%20territories%2C%20belonging%20to%20other%20countries.%20The%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20takes%20strong%20objection%20to%20any%20such%20illegal%20representation%20or%20renaming%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20territories%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20in%20a%20post%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20known%20as%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20leader%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9CChina%E2%80%99s%20deception%20and%20belligerence%20continue%E2%80%9D%20after%20the%20Galwan%20clash%20in%20mid-2020%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Cwake%20of%20PM%20Modi%20giving%20them%20a%20free%20pass%2C%20by%20saying%20%E2%80%98no%20one%20entered%20our%20territory%E2%80%99%2C%20after%2020%20of%20our%20brave%20soldiers%20were%20martyred%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20hope%20that%20the%20G-20%20Summit%20in%20India%2C%20will%20be%20another%20opportunity%20for%20us%20to%20expose%20the%20issue%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%20transgressions%20into%20Indian%20territory%20at%20the%20global%20stage%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20must%20ensure%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%20Chinese%20occupation%20of%202000%20square%20kilometres%20of%20Indian%20territory%20along%20the%20LAC%20must%20end%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20Malliakarjun%20Kharge%E2%80%99s%20reaction%20to%20the%20development%20was%20added%20to%20this%20article%20after%20it%20was%20published.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693286179000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29104346%2FUntitled-design-5-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fnew-china-map-continues-to-show-whole-of-arunachal-pradesh-as-part-of-china%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Such%20a%20representation%20also%20appeared%20on%20previous%20editions.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fnew-china-map-continues-to-show-whole-of-arunachal-pradesh-as-part-of-china%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%